DOC_LEVEL: L2
MODULE: security
PATH: src/security/**
DESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow

KEY_FILES:
- src/security/index.js -> module exports
- src/security/permission-guard.js -> role hierarchy and command authorization
- src/security/param-sanitizer.js -> parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection
- src/security/confirmation-manager.js -> confirmation flow for high-risk actions
- src/security/guard.js -> existing user authorization
- src/security/system-guard.js -> system exec authorization

INTERFACES:
- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'
- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }
- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean
- sanitizeParam(input, options) -> { ok, value?, error? }
- validatePath(path, allowedRoots) -> { ok, resolved?, error? }
- detectDangerousPatterns(input) -> { safe, patterns }
- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }
- checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> { status, action?, params? }
- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }
- cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> void
- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>
- queryAuditLogs(filters) -> Promise<Object[]>

ROLE_HIERARCHY:
- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs
- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry
- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec

COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:
- status, logs: viewer
- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry: operator
- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin

HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:
- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)
- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag

DANGEROUS_PATTERNS:
- path traversal (..)
- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})
- command chains (||, &&, ;)
- home directory expansion (~)
- exec/eval flags

AUDIT_LOG:
- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)
- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId
- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files

TRAPS:
- unknown users default to 'operator' role
- permission denied is logged before returning error
- confirmation expires after 60 seconds
- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)
- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context

DEPENDS_ON:
- src/config.js -> USER_PERMISSIONS, ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM, AUDIT_LOG_*
